setEnvironment

public void setEnvironment(Environment environment)
Description copied from interface: Constraint
Sets the Environment of this Constraint. Environment should come from whatever Component that this Constraint is operating on. Constraint Environment may be set to non-null value only once, further calls are ignored. Application programmer typically never calls this method as Environment is propagated seamlessly.
